title: The Wider Image: In Guatemala, families mourn the migrants who never reached the USA
caption: The journey of Rossanna and Widman began in the Guatemalan village of San Juan La Laguna, on the turquoise Lake Atitlan, where they met when he bought the tortillas she was selling for lunch. It ended in the murky waters of the Rio Grande. The couple drowned as they tried to wade across the notorious part of the river that links Piedras Negras, Mexico, with Eagle Pass, Texas, on Feb. 24, just two among the hundreds of people who lose their lives trying to cross into the U.S. every year. REUTERS/Cheney Orr      SEARCH "ORR MIGRANTS GUATEMALA" FOR THIS STORY. SEARCH "WIDER IMAGE" FOR ALL STORIES.      TPX IMAGES OF THE DAY      TEMPLATE OUT

title: The Wider Image: In Guatemala, families mourn the migrants who never reached the USA
caption: A smuggler, also known as a coyote, from Mexico regains consciousness on the bank of the Rio Grande River after being resuscitated by a man who jumped into the water and dragged him to shore in Piedras Negras, Coahuila, Mexico, February 24, 2024. Minutes earlier, the smuggler led a group of Guatemalan migrants into the river with intentions to cross into Eagle Pass, Texas, U.S. This was the second of two failed crossing attempts made by this group which included Rossanna Azucena Coche Navichoc, 25, and her fiance Widman Alexander Tax Chinic, 26, who were swept downstream by the rushing current and later found dead. REUTERS/Cheney Orr      SEARCH "ORR MIGRANTS GUATEMALA" FOR THIS STORY. SEARCH "WIDER IMAGE" FOR ALL STORIES.

title: The Wider Image: In Guatemala, families mourn the migrants who never reached the USA
caption: Rossanna Azucena Coche Navichoc (left), 25, from Guatemala, her fiance Widman Alexander Tax Chinic (center), 26, and her father Alfredo Navichoc, 45, wade into the Rio Grande River as they attempt to cross into Eagle Pass, Texas, U.S., February 24, 2024. This was the second of two failed crossing attempts made by this group who nearly drowned in the rushing current. Rossana and Widman later became separated from the group, were swept downstream by the strong current and later found dead in Piedras Negras, Coahuila, Mexico. REUTERS/Cheney Orr      SEARCH "ORR MIGRANTS GUATEMALA" FOR THIS STORY. SEARCH "WIDER IMAGE" FOR ALL STORIES.      TPX IMAGES OF THE DAY

title: The Wider Image: In Guatemala, families mourn the migrants who never reached the USA
caption: A Mexican National Guardsman shines a light as a police officer uses a stick to rescue a woman from Colombia who is being swept downstream by the rushing current as she attempts to cross the Rio Grande River into into Eagle Pass, Texas, U.S.,  February 24, 2024. The Colombian woman's rescue occurred less than an hour after a group of migrants from Guatemala had made a separate failed attempt to cross the same section of the river. Among the first group were Rossanna Azucena Coche Navichoc, 25, and her fiance Widman Alexander Tax Chinic, 26, who were swept downstream and later found dead, Piedras Negras, Coahuila, Mexico. REUTERS/Cheney Orr      SEARCH "ORR MIGRANTS GUATEMALA" FOR THIS STORY. SEARCH "WIDER IMAGE" FOR ALL STORIES.

title: The Wider Image: In Guatemala, families mourn the migrants who never reached the USA
caption: Alfredo Navichoc, 45, whose daughter Rossanna Azucena Coche Navichoc, 25, drowned four months ago trying to cross into the U.S., looks across Lake Atitlan from San Juan La Laguna, Guatemala, June 26, 2024. Alfredo survived a failed attempt to cross the Rio Grande River into the U.S. with his daughter Rossanna and her fiance Widman Alexander Tax Chinic, 26, who both drowned. "She wanted to be a chef but we didn't have the money for her to study," said her mother Francisca, 43. "That's why she wanted to go to the USA. She was going to work in a restaurant. I didn't want her to leave but she insisted that five years would give her and Alex the opportunity to raise money to build their own house and open a restaurant here." REUTERS/Cheney Orr      SEARCH "ORR MIGRANTS GUATEMALA" FOR THIS STORY. SEARCH "WIDER IMAGE" FOR ALL STORIES.
